# add 63 days for 6x R-CHOP21    (RCHOP21==0)
# add 42 days for 6x R-CHOP21+1R (RCHOP21==9)
# add 21 days for 6x R-CHOP21+2R (RCHOP21==1) because txstop_rit is almost at the start of the cycle
DLBCL.raw <- DLBCL.raw |>
  mutate(
    at.risk = case_when(
      RCHOP21==0 ~ txstop_rit + lubridate::days(63),
      RCHOP21==9 ~ txstop_rit + lubridate::days(42),
      RCHOP21==1 ~ txstop_rit + lubridate::days(21)
  ))

Propensity score model

  1. RCHOP21 indicates whether the patient received 6x R-CHOP21 or 6x R-CHOP21+2R.
  2. region indicates the region where the patient is treated.
  3. The International Prognostic Index (IPI) consists of
  • an indicator of age > 60 (lft)
  • stage 3 or 4 (stadium)
  • elevated serum LDH (ipi_ldh)
  • WHO score ECOG/Zubrod status 2, 3, or 4 (ipi_ps)
  • more than 1 extranodal site (ipi_extra).
  1. malignancy indicates if a patient had one or more previous malignancy
  2. center indicates if the center that the patient is treated in was academic or not
  3. ses indicates Social Economic Status, which is a proxy for comorbidity, and is divided into low, medium, and high.
# fixed effects propensity score model
PS.formula <- RCHOP21~geslacht+lft+stadium+ipi_ldh+ipi_ps+ipi_extra+malignancy+region+center+ses.low+ses.high
PS.model <- fit.mult.impute(PS.formula, lrm,
                            xtrans=DLBCL,
                            data=to.be.imputed.DLBCL,
                            n.impute=m, pr=FALSE, fit.reps=TRUE,
                            y=TRUE, x=TRUE, se.fit=TRUE)

The propensity score (\(e_i\)), i.e.the predicted probability of treatment, averaged over multiple imputations. Compute sStabilized inverse propensity score weights to be less affected by extremely small weights.

P.Z <- mean(single.imp.DLBCL$RCHOP21)
e.i.imp <- c()
stabilized.w.i.imp <- c()
for (imp in 1:m){
  e.i.imp <- cbind(e.i.imp, plogis(predict(PS.model$fits[[imp]], type="lp", newdata=mice::complete(DLBCL, imp))))
  
  # weights for ith imputed data set
  stabilized.w.i.imp <- cbind(stabilized.w.i.imp, 
                          P.Z*single.imp.DLBCL$RCHOP21/e.i.imp[, imp] +
                          (1-P.Z)*(1-single.imp.DLBCL$RCHOP21)/(1-e.i.imp[, imp]))
}

Recurrence and overall survival

Set time-to-event

The event-free survival indicator (efsi) is 1 if the patient has a recurrence or if there is no response to initial treatment and second line treatment is administered, and 0 otherwise. The time until the event is the event-free survival time.

# omit first events
single.imp.DLBCL.EFS <- single.imp.DLBCL[-which(single.imp.DLBCL$EFS.time<0),]
stabilized.w.i.EFS <- stabilized.w.i.imp[-which(single.imp.DLBCL$EFS.time<0),]

# EFS outcome
single.imp.DLBCL.EFS$S.EFS <- survival::Surv(event=single.imp.DLBCL.EFS$efsi, 
                                             time=single.imp.DLBCL.EFS$EFS.time)

# median follow-up time
med.EFS.time <- stats::quantile(prodlim::prodlim(prodlim::Hist(EFS.time, efsi==1)~1, 
                                                 data=single.imp.DLBCL.EFS, reverse=TRUE))$quantiles.survival

Helper functions

ylabs <- data.frame(outcome=c("EFS", "OS"),
                    label=c("EFS probability", "OS probability"))
limit_year_EFS <- 5
limit_year_OS <- 5

For each outcome, show:

  1. Kaplan-Meier curves
  2. If proportional hazard assumption is satisfied
  3. Kaplan-Meier estimates, hazard ratios and RMST stratified by IPI score
for (outcome in ylabs$outcome){
  # Survival outcome
  S.temp <- eval(parse(text=paste0("single.imp.DLBCL.", outcome, "$S.", outcome)))
  limit_year <- eval(parse(text=(paste0("limit_year_", outcome))))
  
  # Set the censoring of patients with follow-up time more than x years to "censored"
  S.temp[S.temp[,1]>limit_year, 2] <- 0
  # Set the follow-up time to x years for patients with follow-up time more than x years.
  S.temp[S.temp[,1]>limit_year, 1] <- limit_year
  assign(paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit"), S.temp)
  
  # Kaplan-Meier plots
  km <- survival::survfit(eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit ~ RCHOP21"))),
                          data=eval(parse(text=paste0("single.imp.DLBCL.", outcome))), 
                          weights=eval(parse(text=paste0("rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.", outcome, ")"))),
                          robust=TRUE, type="kaplan-meier", conf.type="log")
  assign(paste0("km_", outcome), km)

  # Kaplan-Meier estimates at x-years
  treat <- summary(km, times=limit_year)
  ARD <- diff(treat$surv)
  ARD_text <- paste0(sprintf("%.1f", ARD*100), "%")
  assign(paste0("ARD_", outcome), ARD)
  ARD_se <- sqrt(sum((treat$std.err)^2))
  ARD_CI_text <- paste0(sprintf("%.1f", (ARD-1.96*ARD_se)*100),
                   "-", sprintf("%.1f", (ARD+1.96*ARD_se)*100))
  assign(paste0("ARD_CI_", outcome), ARD_CI_text)
    
  # Log-rank test using stabilized weights is rejected,
  # thus the survival between the two treatment groups is significantly different
  LRT <- RISCA::ipw.log.rank(times=eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit[, 1]"))), 
                             failures=eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit[, 2]"))),
                             variable=eval(parse(text=paste0("single.imp.DLBCL.", outcome, "$RCHOP21"))), 
                             weights=eval(parse(text=paste0("rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.", outcome, ")"))))
  LRT_text <- sprintf("%.2f", LRT$p.value)
  
  # Univariate Cox proportional hazards model with stabilized weights
  cox <- survival::coxph(eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit ~ RCHOP21"))),
                         data=eval(parse(text=paste0("single.imp.DLBCL.", outcome))),
                         weights=eval(parse(text=paste0("rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.", outcome, ")"))),
                         robust=TRUE)
  HR <- exp(coef(cox))
  HR_text <- sprintf("%.2f", HR)
  HR_text_lower <- sprintf("%.2f", exp(confint(cox)[, "2.5 %"]))
  HR_text_upper <- sprintf("%.2f", exp(confint(cox)[, "97.5 %"]))
  
  # Restricted Mean Survival Time Analysis
  RMST <- survival:::survmean(km, rmean=limit_year)
  dRMST <- diff(RMST$matrix[, "rmean"])
  dRMST_text <- sprintf("%.2f", dRMST)
  assign(paste0("dRMST_", outcome), dRMST_text)
  dRMST_se <- RMST$matrix[, "se(rmean)"]
  dRMST_CI_text <- paste0(sprintf("%.2f", dRMST-1.96*sqrt(sum(dRMST_se^2))), 
                          "-", sprintf("%.2f", dRMST+1.96*sqrt(sum(dRMST_se^2))))
  assign(paste0("dRMST_CI_", outcome), dRMST_CI_text)
  
  # Kaplan-Meier plot
  km_plot <- survminer::ggsurvplot(km,
                                  palette=c("#EC7F12", "#9161BD"),
                                  ggtheme = theme(
                                    axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
                                    panel.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                                    plot.background = element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                                    panel.grid.major = element_blank(), #remove major gridlines
                                    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), #remove minor gridlines
                                    legend.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white legend bg
                                    legend.box.background = element_rect(color = NA, fill='white') #white legend panel
                                  ),
                                  legend.labs=c("6x R-CHOP21", "6x R-CHOP21+2R"),
                                  xlab="",
                                  ylab=ylabs[ylabs$outcome==outcome, "label"],
                                  risk.table=FALSE, conf.int="True",
                                  robust=TRUE, pval=FALSE)$plot+
                ggplot2::annotate("text", x=0, y=0.05,
                                  label=paste0("p-value of weighted log-rank test = ",
                                               LRT_text, "\n",
                                               "HR = ", HR_text,
                                               paste0(", 95% CI: ",
                                                      HR_text_lower, "-",
                                                      HR_text_upper, "\n"),
                                               "ARD = ", ARD_text, 
                                               paste0(", 95% CI: ", ARD_CI_text), "\n",
                                               "\u0394RMST = ", dRMST_text,
                                               paste0(", 95% CI: ", dRMST_CI_text), "\n"),
                                  size=3.5, hjust=0)
  assign(paste0("km_plot_", outcome), km_plot)
  km_table <- survminer::ggsurvplot(km,
                                    palette=c("#EC7F12", "#9161BD"),
                                    ggtheme = theme(
                                       axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
                                       panel.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                                       plot.background = element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                                       panel.grid.major = element_blank(), #remove major gridlines
                                       panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), #remove minor gridlines
                                       legend.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white legend bg
                                       legend.box.background = element_rect(fill='white') #white legend panel
                                    ),
                                    legend.labs=c("-2R", "+2R"),
                                    xlab="Time in years",
                                    risk.table=TRUE,
                                    robust=TRUE,
                                    pval=FALSE)$table
  assign(paste0("km_table_", outcome), km_table)

  # Write results to Excel
  openxlsx::write.xlsx(x=data.frame(names=c("6x R-CHOP21", "6x R-CHOP21+2R", "Difference", "P-value"),
           KMest=c(sprintf("%.1f", treat$surv*100),
                   sprintf("%.1f", ARD*100),
                   LRT_text),
           KMCI=c(paste0(sprintf("%.1f", treat$lower*100), 
                         "-", sprintf("%.1f", treat$upper*100)),
                  ARD_CI_text, 
                  ""),
           Coxest=c("(ref)",
                    HR_text,
                    "",
                    as.numeric(sprintf("%.2f", summary(cox)$robscore["pvalue"]))),
           CoxCI=c("",
                   paste0(HR_text_lower, "-",
                          HR_text_upper),
                   "",
                   ""),
           RMSTest=c("",
                     "",
                     dRMST_text,
                     ""),
           RMSTCI=c("",
                    "",
                    dRMST_CI_text,
                    "")),
           file=paste0(file.path, "Results/overall.", outcome , ".xlsx"),
           sheetName=outcome)
}

# Subgroup analysis stratified by IPI score

# obtain average IPI score across multiple imputations
comb.ipi.imp.EFS <- c()
comb.ipi.imp.OS <- c()
for (imp in 1:m){
  comb.ipi.imp.EFS <- cbind(comb.ipi.imp.EFS, mice::complete(DLBCL, imp)[-which(single.imp.DLBCL$EFS.time<0), "ipi_score"])
  comb.ipi.imp.OS <- cbind(comb.ipi.imp.OS, mice::complete(DLBCL, imp)[, "ipi_score"])
}
combined.IPI.EFS <- round(rowMeans(comb.ipi.imp.EFS), 0)
combined.IPI.OS <- round(rowMeans(comb.ipi.imp.OS), 0)

for (outcome in ylabs$outcome){
  # estimate treatment effect in each quartile
  limit_year <- eval(parse(text=(paste0("limit_year_", outcome))))
  KM_est_quartile <- c()
  plot_KM <- list()
  table_KM <- list()
  HR_quartile <- c()
  HR_quartile_lower <- c()
  HR_quartile_upper <- c()
  dRMST_quartiles <- c()
  dRMST_quartiles_lower <- c()
  dRMST_quartiles_upper <- c()
  LRT_stat_quartile <- c()
  LRT_p_quartile <- c()
  for (ipi.i in 1:g){
    # select data for only ith quartile
    quartile.DLBCL <- eval(parse(text=paste0("single.imp.DLBCL.", outcome, "[combined.IPI.", outcome, "==ipi.i,]")))
    quartile.stabilized.w.i <- eval(parse(text=paste0("rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.", outcome, "[combined.IPI.", outcome, "==ipi.i,])")))
    
    # Survival outcome
    S.quartile <- eval(parse(text=paste0("quartile.DLBCL$S.", outcome)))
    # Set the censoring of patients with follow-up time more than x years to "censored"
    S.quartile[S.quartile[,1]>limit_year, 2] <- 0
    # Set the follow-up time to x years for patients with follow-up time more than x years.
    S.quartile[S.quartile[,1]>limit_year, 1] <- limit_year
    quartile.DLBCL$S.quartile <- S.quartile

    # event-free survival at 5 years
    km_quartile <- survival::survfit(S.quartile~RCHOP21, 
                                     data=quartile.DLBCL, robust=TRUE,
                                     weights=quartile.stabilized.w.i,
                                     type="kaplan-meier", conf.type="log")
    # save survival
    treat_quartile <- summary(km_quartile, times = limit_year)
    KM_est_quartile <- rbind(KM_est_quartile,
                             cbind(treat_quartile$surv, treat_quartile$std.err,
                                   treat_quartile$lower, treat_quartile$upper))
    
    # log-rank test
    LRT_quartile <- RISCA::ipw.log.rank(times=S.quartile[, 1], failures=S.quartile[, 2],
                      variable=quartile.DLBCL$RCHOP21,
                      weights=quartile.stabilized.w.i)
    LRT_stat_quartile <- c(LRT_stat_quartile, LRT_quartile$statistic)
    LRT_p_quartile <- c(LRT_p_quartile, LRT_quartile$p.value)

    # univariate cox
    cox_quartile <- survival::coxph(S.quartile~RCHOP21, data=quartile.DLBCL,
                                  weights=quartile.stabilized.w.i,
                                  robust=TRUE)
    PH.assumption <- survival::cox.zph(cox_quartile)$table["RCHOP21", "p"]

    # save hazard ratios
    HR_quartile <- c(HR_quartile, as.numeric(exp(coef(cox_quartile)[1])))
    HR_quartile_lower <- c(HR_quartile_lower, as.numeric(exp(confint(cox_quartile)[1,1])))
    HR_quartile_upper <- c(HR_quartile_upper, as.numeric(exp(confint(cox_quartile)[1,2])))

    # RMST
    RMST_quartile <- survival:::survmean(km_quartile, rmean=limit_year)
    dRMST_Q <- diff(RMST_quartile$matrix[, "rmean"])
    dRMST_quartiles <- c(dRMST_quartiles, dRMST_Q)
    RMST_text_quartile <- sprintf("%.1f", dRMST_Q)
    
    dRMST_Q_se <- RMST_quartile$matrix[, "se(rmean)"]
    dRMST_quartiles_lower <- c(dRMST_quartiles_lower, dRMST_Q-1.96*sqrt(sum(dRMST_Q_se^2)))
    dRMST_quartiles_upper <- c(dRMST_quartiles_upper, dRMST_Q+1.96*sqrt(sum(dRMST_Q_se^2)))
    
    # make text for KM plots
    LRT_text_quartile <- sprintf("%.1f", LRT_quartile$p.value)
    HR_text_quartile <- sprintf("%.1f", exp(coef(cox_quartile)[1]))
    HR_text_quartile_lower <- sprintf("%.1f", exp(confint(cox_quartile)[1,1]))
    HR_text_quartile_upper <- sprintf("%.1f", exp(confint(cox_quartile)[1,2]))
    
    # save Kaplan-Meier plots
    plot_KM[[ipi.i]] <- survminer::ggsurvplot(km_quartile, 
                                              conf.int="True",
                                              palette=c("#EC7F12", "#9161BD"),
                                              ggtheme = ggplot2::theme(
                                                 axis.line = ggplot2::element_line(colour = "black"),
                                                 panel.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                                                 plot.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                                                 panel.grid.major = ggplot2::element_blank(), #remove major gridlines
                                                 panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank(), #remove minor gridlines
                                                 legend.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white'), #white legend bg
                                                 legend.box.background = ggplot2::element_rect(km_plot, fill='white') #white legend panel
                                              ),
                                              ylim=c(0, 1), risk.table=TRUE)$plot+
    ggplot2::theme(legend.position = "none")+
    ggplot2::ylab(ylabs[ylabs$outcome==outcome, "label"])+
    ggplot2::xlab("")+
    ggplot2::theme(plot.title=ggplot2::element_text(hjust=0.5, size=10),
           axis.text.x=ggplot2::element_text(size=10),
           axis.title.x=ggplot2::element_text(size=10),
           axis.text.y=ggplot2::element_text(size=10),
           axis.title.y=ggplot2::element_text(size=10))+
    ggplot2::ggtitle(paste0("(N=", nrow(quartile.DLBCL), ")")) 
            
    # save Kaplan-Meier risk table
    table_KM[[ipi.i]] <- survminer::ggsurvplot(km_quartile,
      palette=c("#EC7F12", "#9161BD"),
      ggtheme = theme(axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
                      axis.text.y = ggplot2::element_text(size=10),
                      axis.title.y = ggplot2::element_text(size=10),
                      axis.line.y = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      axis.ticks.y = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      axis.line.x = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      axis.ticks.x = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      axis.text.x = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      axis.title.x = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                      panel.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                      plot.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                      panel.grid.major = ggplot2::element_blank(), #remove major gridlines
                      panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank(), #remove minor gridlines
                      legend.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white'), #white legend bg
                      legend.box.background = ggplot2::element_rect(fill='white') #white legend panel
      ),
      legend.labs=c("-2R", "+2R"),
      xlab="Time in years",
      risk.table=TRUE,
      risk.table.title=element_blank(),
      risk.table.fontsize=3,
      robust=TRUE, pval=FALSE)$table
  }

  # combine Kaplan-Meier estimates into one data frame
  KM_est_quartile <- cbind(KM_est_quartile, rep(c(0, 1), g))
  KM_est_quartile <- cbind(KM_est_quartile, rep(1:g, each=2))
  colnames(KM_est_quartile) <- c("estimate", "sd", "lower", "upper", "treatment", "risk.group")
  KM_est_quartile <- as.data.frame(KM_est_quartile)
  assign(paste0("KM_est_quartile_", outcome), KM_est_quartile)

  # combine hazard ratios into one data frame
  HR_df_quartile <- data.frame(risk.group=1:g, estimate=HR_quartile, 
                               lower=HR_quartile_lower, upper=HR_quartile_upper)

  # combine RMST into one data frame
  dRMST_df_quartile <- data.frame(risk.group=1:g, estimate=dRMST_quartiles, 
                                 lower=dRMST_quartiles_lower, upper=dRMST_quartiles_upper)
  assign(paste0("dRMST_df_quartile_", outcome), dRMST_df_quartile)
  
  # Calculate the absolute difference in event-free survival, i.e. benefit and harm.
  diff <- c()
  j <- 1
  for (i in seq(from=1, to=nrow(KM_est_quartile), by=2)){
    diff <- rbind(diff, KM_est_quartile[i+1,]-KM_est_quartile[i,])

    # standard deviation of difference is square root of sum of variances
    diff[j, "sd"] <- sqrt(KM_est_quartile[i+1, "sd"]^2+KM_est_quartile[i, "sd"]^2)
    diff[j, "lower"] <- diff[j, "estimate"]-1.96*diff[j, "sd"]
    diff[j, "upper"] <- diff[j, "estimate"]+1.96*diff[j, "sd"]
    j <- j + 1
  }
  diff <- as.data.frame(diff)
  diff$risk.group <- 1:g
  ARD_df_quartile <- data.frame(risk.group=1:g, estimate=diff$estimate*100, 
                                lower=diff$lower*100, upper=diff$upper*100)
  assign(paste0("ARD_df_quartile_", outcome), ARD_df_quartile)

  # Write results to Excel
  results.df.q <- data.frame(cbind(c(rep("ARD", 4), rep("HR", 4), rep("RMST", 4)),
                              rbind(ARD_df_quartile,
                                    HR_df_quartile,
                                    dRMST_df_quartile)))
  results.df.q$text <- paste0(sprintf("%.2f", results.df.q$estimate), ", 95% CI:", 
                              sprintf("%.2f", results.df.q$lower), "; ", 
                              sprintf("%.2f", results.df.q$upper))
  openxlsx::write.xlsx(results.df.q,
           file=paste0(file.path, "Results/IPI.stratified.", outcome, ".xlsx"),
           sheetName=outcome)
  cat(outcome, "ARD Q4:", sprintf("%.1f", results.df.q$estimate[4]), ", 95% CI:", 
                 sprintf("%.1f", results.df.q$lower[4]), "; ", 
                 sprintf("%.1f", results.df.q$upper[4]), "\n")

  # Kaplan-Meier plots
  KM_plots <- ggpubr::ggarrange(plot_KM[[1]]+ggplot2::labs(tag="A"),
                                plot_KM[[2]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                plot_KM[[3]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                plot_KM[[4]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                ncol=4, nrow=1,
                                widths=c(1, 0.8, 0.8, 0.8),
                                align="h")
  
  # Kaplan-Meier tables
  table_KM_plots <- ggpubr::ggarrange(table_KM[[1]],
                                table_KM[[2]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                table_KM[[3]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                table_KM[[4]]+ggpubr::rremove("y.axis")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("ylab")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.text")+
                                  ggpubr::rremove("y.ticks"),
                                ncol=4, nrow=1,
                                widths=c(1, 0.8, 0.8, 0.8),
                                align="h")
  
  # plot for absolute reduction in survival
  avg.diff <- diff(summary(eval(parse(text=paste0("km_", outcome))),
                           times = limit_year)$surv)
  ARD.plot <- ggplot2::ggplot(data=diff,
                              ggplot2::aes(x=factor(risk.group), y=estimate))+
    ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=0)+
    ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=avg.diff, linetype="dashed", linewidth=1.2)+
    ggplot2::geom_errorbar(ggplot2::aes(ymin=lower, ymax=upper),
                           position=ggplot2::position_dodge(0.9), width=0)+
    ggplot2::geom_point(size=5, shape=18, color="#EC7F12")+
    ggplot2::scale_y_continuous(limits=c(min(diff$lower, -0.2), max(diff$upper, 0.4)),
                                breaks=seq(-0.2, 0.4, 0.2),
                                labels=scales::percent_format(accuracy=1))+
    ggplot2::theme(text=ggplot2::element_text(size=12),
                   axis.line.y = element_line(colour = "black"),
                   panel.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                   plot.background = element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                   panel.grid.major = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                   panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank())+
    ggplot2::ylab("ARD") + 
    ggplot2::theme(axis.title.x=ggplot2::element_blank(),
                   axis.text.x=ggplot2::element_blank(),
                   axis.ticks.x=ggplot2::element_blank())+
    ggplot2::labs(tag="C")
  
  # test for multiplicative HTE
  DLBCL.temp <- eval(parse(text=paste0("single.imp.DLBCL.", outcome)))
  S.temp <- eval(parse(text=paste0("S.", outcome, ".limit")))
  ipi.temp <- eval(parse(text=paste0("combined.IPI.", outcome)))
  test.HR <- summary(coxph(S.temp ~ RCHOP21*ipi.temp, 
                           data=DLBCL.temp,
                           weights=eval(parse(text=paste0("rowMeans(stabilized.w.i.", 
                                                          outcome, ")")))))$coefficients[3, "Pr(>|z|)"]
  
  # create plot for hazard ratios
  hazard.plot <- ggplot2::ggplot(data=HR_df_quartile, ggplot2::aes(x=risk.group, y=estimate))+
    ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=1)+
    ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=HR, linetype="dashed", linewidth=1.2)+
    ggplot2::geom_errorbar(ggplot2::aes(ymin=lower, ymax=upper),
                           position=ggplot2::position_dodge(0.9), width=0)+
    ggplot2::geom_point(size=5, shape=18, color="#EC7F12")+
    ggplot2::scale_x_discrete(limits=as.factor(1:g))+
    ggplot2::scale_y_continuous(limits=c(min(HR_df_quartile$lower, 0.5), 
                                         max(HR_df_quartile$upper, 2)),
                                breaks=seq(0.5, 2, 0.5),
                                labels=scales::number_format(accuracy=0.01))+
    ggplot2::theme(text=ggplot2::element_text(size=12),
                    axis.title.x=ggplot2::element_blank(),
                    axis.text.x=ggplot2::element_blank(),
                    axis.ticks.x=ggplot2::element_blank(),
                    axis.line.y = element_line(colour = "black"),
                    panel.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                    plot.background = element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                    panel.grid.major = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                    panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank())+
    ggplot2::ylab("Hazard ratio")+
    ggplot2::geom_text(mapping=aes(x=g, y=2, 
                                   label=paste0("p-value = ", sprintf("%.2f", test.HR))),
                       hjust=0, size=3)+
    ggplot2::labs(tag="B")

  # create plot for RMST
  dRMST.plot <- ggplot2::ggplot(data=dRMST_df_quartile, ggplot2::aes(x=risk.group, y=estimate))+
    ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=0)+
    ggplot2::geom_hline(yintercept=dRMST, linetype="dashed", linewidth=1.2)+
    ggplot2::geom_errorbar(ggplot2::aes(ymin=lower, ymax=upper),
                           position=ggplot2::position_dodge(0.9), width=0)+
    ggplot2::geom_point(size=5, shape=18, color="#EC7F12")+
    ggplot2::scale_x_discrete(limits=c("1"="IPI score 0-1", "2"="IPI score 2", "3"="IPI score 3", "4"="IPI score 4-5"))+
    ggplot2::scale_y_continuous(limits=c(min(dRMST_df_quartile$lower, -0.25), 
                                         max(dRMST_df_quartile$upper, 1)),
                                breaks=seq(-0.25, 1, 0.25),
                                labels=scales::number_format(accuracy=0.01))+
    ggplot2::theme(text=ggplot2::element_text(size=12),
                    axis.line.y = element_line(colour = "black"),
                    panel.background = element_rect(fill='white'), #white panel bg
                    plot.background = element_rect(fill='white', color=NA), #white plot bg
                    panel.grid.major = ggplot2::element_blank(),
                    panel.grid.minor = ggplot2::element_blank())+
    ggplot2::xlab("IPI score")+
    ggplot2::ylab("\u0394RMST")+
    ggplot2::labs(tag="D")
  
  # save plot
  ggsave(filename=paste0(file.path, "Results/Figure IPI-stratified ", outcome, ".png"),
       plot=ggpubr::ggarrange(KM_plots, table_KM_plots,
                              hazard.plot / ARD.plot / dRMST.plot, 
                              nrow=3, ncol=1, heights=c(5, 2, 10)),
       width=8, height=8, dpi=300)
}
